The trigger mechanism of the weapon and the fire control handle are combined with a block attached to the lower wall of the receiver. Before and above the handle there are levers for controlling the magazine latch and the fire translator, which is also a fuse, which allows you to control the weapon with just one hand. double-row magazines for 20 and 30 rounds or from disk magazines for 50 and 100 rounds (only box magazines in the M1A1 and M1 models). For disk magazines, the receiver was equipped with transverse grooves [78]. or until it's over cartridges.